{"books":{"10":{"id":"4774","title":"All of Grace","description":"<p>HE WHO SPOKE and wrote this message will be greatly disappointed if it does not lead many to the Lord Jesus. It is sent forth in childlike dependence upon the power of God the Holy Ghost, to use it in the conversion of millions, if so He pleases. No doubt many poor men and women will take up this little volume, and the Lord will visit them with grace. To answer this end, the very plainest language has been chosen, and many homely expressions have been used. But if those of wealth and rank should glance at this book, the Holy Ghost can impress them also; since that which can be understood by the unlettered is none the less attractive to the instructed. Oh that some might read it who will become great winners of souls! <br><\/br>\n\nWho knows how many will find their way to peace by what they read here? A more important question to you, dear reader, is this \u2013 Will you be one of them? (From All of Grace)<\/p>","url_text_source":"http:\/\/www.ccel.org\/ccel\/spurgeon\/grace.html","language":"English","copyright_year":"1892","num_sections":"11","url_rss":"http:\/\/librivox.org\/rss\/4774","url_zip_file":"http:\/\/www.archive.org\/download\/all_of_grace_1011_librivox\/all_of_grace_1011_librivox_64kb_mp3.zip","url_project":"","url_librivox":"http:\/\/librivox.org\/all-of-grace-by-charles-h-spurgeon\/","url_other":null,"totaltime":"3:30:00","totaltimesecs":12600,"authors":[{"id":"1490","first_name":"Charles H.","last_name":"Spurgeon","dob":"1834","dod":"1892"}],"url_iarchive":"http:\/\/www.archive.org\/details\/all_of_grace_1011_librivox","sections":[{"id":"47459","section_number":"1","title":"01 - What Are We At?","listen_url":"http:\/\/upload.librivox.org\/share\/uploads\/avs\/allgrace_01_spurgeon.mp3","language":"English","playtime":"386","file_name":null,"readers":[{"reader_id":"3645","display_name":"MaryAnn"}]},{"id":"47460","section_number":"2","title":"02 - God Justifieth The Ungodly","listen_u